Detailed Description

Data class that represents world intersection related data output by the Tracking Engine This is a base class and all its derived classes will share this interface.

virtual int32 intersectionObjectIndex (  )  const [virtual]

Index of the world-model object intersected by the direction vector.

The world model contains a number of indexed objects. The field contains the index of the object that is intersected, or -1 if no object is intersected or the tracking failed. The value is only valid if >=1.

Note that this does not include the screen, which is a special world model object.

Reimplemented in GazeIntersectionOutputDataV1, GazeIntersectionOutputDataV2, and HeadIntersectionOutputDataV1.

virtual const std::string intersectionObjectName (  )  const [virtual]

Name of the world-model object intersected by the direction vector.

The world model contains a number of indexed objects. The field contains the name of the object that is intersected, or "nothing" if no object is intersected or "notrack" if the tracking failed.

Note:
This name can be any length, but when this object is serialized, the name will be truncated/padded to ensure it is exactly MAX_OBJ_NAME_LENGTH

Reimplemented in GazeIntersectionOutputDataV1, GazeIntersectionOutputDataV2, and HeadIntersectionOutputDataV1.
